</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I've been playing my wizard lately, (35, can't port everywhere, but that's still a port bitch) I get asked for ports left and right. Frankly I only port friends for free. When random person_01 sends me a tell asking for a port I usually reply with "I'm busy, it will take some "convincing" to get me to leave" <br><br>People who don't pay when they offer, are just ass holes. I never click the gem unless I have been paid what they offered. 1pp for all I care, you offer, you pay. No pay? No port. That simple. If they had come up saying they were on a CR, things would be different. <p><center><table width=350 border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr valign="top"><td align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35013" TARGET="_top"><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/fierios/newsig.txt" WIDTH="350" HEIGHT="215"><br> Click here to view my inventory</a></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ushinryuumoondancer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shinryuu Moondancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 10:26:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3106.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I never asked money for ports, and most of the time i refused the offers (especially when its a cleric who is asking).<br>I never had or will have a big bank account, but sometimes im running low and will accept the (sometime generous) offers.<br><br>I do understand its sometimes annoying (especially when the folks are X zones away asking for port).. so mostly im anon and hide my familiar...<br>And yes, there are retarded 