ren't busy and willing to help.. the desire to give away pp overcomes me<br><br>If I have money on me, I ALWAYS donate.  I've done a /split after they refused and had them give it back to me.<br><br>If I just loaned someone my last pp or am naked going for my corpse, I make sure the person helping me when they know I cant pay them anything in return can call on me anytime for help.  Whether it be summoning a corpse out of the ocean or even just helping them break up a spawn.<br><br>Guess I'm saying thanks for all those times that porting people helped me and would take nothing in return. <p><a href="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" border="0" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=222></a> <BR> ~Dalamarn Darkgem~ <BR>~Harbinger of Death~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 12:20:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3106.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Port Customer Ettiquette</span><hr size=1> 1.  Announce your desire in a public channel.  /ooc, /shout, or even /auc (/auc BUYING:  Port/TL to DL for 30 pp works amazing well in EC. Hee hee.).<br><br>2.  Do not /tell individual wizard/druid in zone after you've done the public channel.  Guess what, they can read and if they haven't responded to your /ooc, /shout, /auc, they probably aren't going to give in to a /tell either.<br><br>3.  Donate.  /split works great cuz it gets around the entire wait for click of trade buttons (some people's pointer lags REAL bad in Kunark or EC tunnel).  Also, it doesn't force them to be modest either.  We're using them for our comfort, they deserve renumeration.<br><br>4.  /disband on TLs.  There is NO reason for the wizard to have to wait for you to finish zoning if (s)he suddenly needs to accept an invite.  So when you see the TL confirmation box, type /disband first, then click YES (or OK or whatever it is).  That way you have no chance of bugging the wizard or what have you.<br><br>5.  Say thank you.  Doesn't matter if you've already payed 200 pp for the port/TL, there is a person behind that toon.  They are not an NPC merchant vendor with auto click.  If you value their services enough to offer plat or another form of donation, respect them as a person and say &quot;Thank you&quot;.  Also, don't say &quot;thx&quot; or &quot;ty&quot; or what have you.  Type the extra 6 or 7 characters to actually speak English. They just sit down, unmemmed a spell, memmed a spell, got into a group with you, cast the spell, will need to unmem the spell, remem the spell they need next, and (unless it's a TL) actually zone.  You can type 7 letters.<br><br>6.  Don't being a lying scum bag.  If you say you are going to donate, donate.  If you can't donate, don't say you will.  This is more than courtesy, this is an issue of character.  Do you really think that a wizard doesn't have friends and that they aren't going to hear about you stiffing them?  Do you really think that these friends are going to say to themselves, &quot;Or sure, Scumbag_01 stiff my friend the wizard, but that was just a port.  Sure we can trust him/her not to ninja loot on this raid.&quot;? Guess again.  You rep is very important in EQ and this is just another way to destroy it.<br><br>These are the rules I follow for porting.  It's very simple really...it's just make a natural assumption that there is an actual PERSON behind the person who is porting me.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com"><img src=http://www.zipcon.net/~brus/salenie_sig.jpg></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugremer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gremer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 12:30:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3106.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Just a word of advice.....every Wizzie (or Cleric, LOL) knows what the question "Are you busy?" means.  Rather than go through a tedious process of questions and answers, I'd MUCH prefer to get all the information up front, i.e., "Hello there, sorry to bother you but I am in need of a port or TL to DL.  I am currently at the GD portal and will gladly donate 20pp for your time."  That tells me everything I need to know....where you are, where you need to go, etc.<br><br>It's hugely frustrating to get the "hello" tells and then have to laboriously go through this:<br><br>"hello to you as well"<br>"are you busy?"<br>"no, not especially"<br>"do you have time for a port"<br>"sure, where are you?"<br>"I'm in GD"<br>"Could you be a bit more specific?"<br>"I'm not sure....tell me where you are and I'll find you"<br>"I'm at the GD portal"<br>"Can you give me the location?"<br>"It's at pos 3000 pos 3000"<br>"What direction is that from me?"<br>"...."<br><br>And so on...... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr